          "explanation": "Neurogenic shock is a distributive type of shock resulting in low blood pressure, occasionally with a slowed hea rate, that is attributed to the disruption of the autonomic pathways within the spinal cord. It can occur after damage to the central nervous system, such as spinal cord injury and traumatic brain injury. Ref -davidson 23rd edtion pg 1148",
          "hint": "Topic: Miscellaneous"
