          "id": "medmcqa-103017e3-b606-4e18-8dbf-16bd7144f2a8",
          "text": "A 60-year-old woman with no past medical history has an elevated blood pressure of 165/80 mm Hg on routine evaluation. Repeated measurements over the next month confirm the elevated pressure. Physical examination, routine blood count, and biochemistry are all normalFor patient with high blood pressure, select the most appropriate medication",
