          "correctOptionId": "opt-1",
          "explanation": "Cardiac amyloidosis may affect the way electrical signals move through the hea (conduction system). This can lead to abnormal heabeats (arrhythmias) and faulty hea signals (hea block). The condition can be inherited. This is called familial cardiac amyloidosis Ref Davidson 23rd edition pg 456",
