          "id": "medmcqa-a006d753-e819-4876-8108-217d0450d732",
          "text": "A 4-year-old male child presents with muscles weakness. His mother tells that her child has difficulty in climbing stairs and getting up from the floor. On muscle biopsy, small muscle fibrils and absent of dystrophic was found. What is the diagnosis out of given option?",
