          "explanation": "From the history and clinical findings,the patient is having chronic obstructive pulmonary disease-emphysematous type.it is characterised by hyperinflation of lungs with low set diaphragm.Breath sounds are typically quiet.Right hea failure and cor pulmonale can occur in severe cases,evident as bilateral pitting pedal edema. Ref:Harrison's medicine-18th edition,page no:2156;Davidson's medicine-22nd edition,page no:674.",
