          "explanation": "Hepatitis D virus Hepatitis D accounts for maximum number of fulminant cases of viral hepatitis, a sizable propoion of which are associated with HBV infection. Superinfection with HDV in patients of chronic hepatitis B infection leads to fulminant hepatic failure",
          "hint": "Topic: Hepatic encephalopathy & hepatic failure"
