          "explanation": "Botulism is caused by neurotoxins of Clostridium botulinum, which are extremely potent & cause disease after ingestion of even picogram amounts. Its classical form is an acute onset of bilateral cranial neuropathies associated with symmetric descending weakness.The toxin causes predominantly bulbar & ocular palsies(difficulty in swallowing ,blurred or double vision ,ptosis),progressive to limb weakness & respiratory paralysis . Reference Harrison20th edition pg 1027",
