          "id": "medmcqa-63497dfb-a998-4137-9888-40d31588e79c",
          "text": "A 63-year-old man presents to the emergency department because of transient symptoms of vertigo, slurred speech, diplopia, and paresthesia. He is symptom-free now, and clinical examination is entirely normal. His past medical history is significant for osteoarthritis, hypertension, and dyslipidemia. Which of the following is the most likely cause for symptoms?",
