          "explanation": "Child-Pugh score is calculated by adding the scores of the five factors and can range from 5 to 15. Decompensation indicates cirrhosis with a Child-Pugh score of >7 (class B). This level has been the accepted criterion for listing liver transplantation. Parameters: Bilirubin INR Albumin Ascites Asterixis Grade Points One-year Patient Survival (%) A: well-compensated disease 5-6 100 B: significant function compromise 7-9 80 C: decompensated disease 10-15 45",
