          "explanation": "Microalbuminuria (<300 mg/day or <300mg/d) shows that diabetic nephropathy is reversible. Overt proteinuria ie >300mg/d is usually irreversible. \nThe most common histological pattern in DM is Diffuse Glomerulosclerosis. \nThe most typical histological pattern in DM is Kimmelstiel-Wilson lesion (nodular glomerulosclerosis)."
