          "explanation": "Answer is A (CA 125) : Manual of Clinical Surgery by Kirk CA 125 is the most commonly used tumor marker for ovarian cancer - Kirk CA-125 is found in derivatives of Coelomic epithelium, including pleura pericardium and peritoneum but is not detected in normal ovarian tissue."
