          "explanation": "The patient is suffering from resistant hypeension and the leading cause of resistant hypeension is non- compliance on the pa of patient. Resistant hypeension is defined as blood pressure that remains above goal in spite of the concurrent use of 3 antihypeensive agents of different classes. Ideally, one of the 3 agents should be a diuretic and all agents should be prescribed at optimal dose amounts.",
