          "explanation": "Answer is D (Hypocalcemia): Addison's disease may he associated with Hypercakemia and not hypocafremia. In Addison's disease Hypercalcemia occurs in 10-20% of patients due to unclear reasons - Harrison Addison 's disease may be associated with Hyperkalemia, Hvponatremia and hypotension as explained in the previous question."
